    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>One batch of pink paint uses 2 cups of red paint and 7 cups of white paint. How many batches could you make using 10 cups of red paint and 35 cups of white paint? Explain your reasoning.</p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>5 batches. 5 batches of pink paint will require 10 cups of red paint because there are 2 cups of&#xA0;red paint in 1 batch and that amount will need to be multiplied by 5 and <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="38706">\(5 \boldcdot 2 = 10\)</span>. It will also require 35 cups of white paint because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45260">\(5 \boldcdot 7 = 35\)</span>.</p>
</div>
